== RubyCocoa

During development I run the RubyCocoa edge code.

Get it:
$ svn co https://rubycocoa.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/rubycocoa/trunk/src rubycocoa

Build it:
$ cd rubycocoa
$ ruby install.rb config
$ ruby install.rb setup

Test it (thread tests will fail! it needs a patched libruby):
$ ruby install.rb test

Install it:
$ sudo ruby install.rb install

== Kari.app

Adjust CampKari.rb to your env. E.g. if you use a macports ruby:
  @camp_kari.launchPath = '/opt/local/bin/camping'
  ...
  @camp_kari.environment = { 'PATH' => '/opt/local/bin', 'HOME' => ENV['HOME'] }

Build/Run it:
$ rake run